actor Editor as Organization media/webhook manager
actor Consumer as Delivery API consumer
participant Tenant as Auth and tenant middleware
participant Media as Media route
participant Inspect as MIME/signature checks
participant Image as Image processor
participant FS as Local upload filesystem
participant DB as PostgreSQL
participant Delivery as Delivery API route
participant Cache as Redis cache service
participant Webhook as Webhook routes/service
participant Receiver as External webhook consumer

rect rgb(238, 247, 255)
    Note over Editor,DB: Multipart media upload [IMPLEMENTED, NON-ATOMIC FILE/DB LIFECYCLE]
    Editor->>Tenant: POST /api/media/upload multipart with Bearer token and organization header
    Tenant->>Media: Claims, TenantContext, and body under configured limit
    Media->>Media: require_org_media_writer
    critical Multipart parsing and preflight [IMPLEMENTED]
        Media->>Media: Read alt_text, caption, and file bytes
        Media->>Media: Enforce configured max_upload_size
        Media->>Inspect: Detect MIME from file signature/content
        Inspect->>Inspect: Allow JPEG, PNG, WebP, PDF, or UTF-8 text only
        Inspect->>Inspect: Compare declared MIME unless octet-stream
        Media->>DB: Check organization media quota
    option Missing/oversized/unsupported/mismatched/quota-exceeding file
        Media-->>Editor: Validation or quota error before filesystem write
    end
    Media->>FS: Create {upload_dir}/{organization_id}/variants
    Media->>FS: Write original file using generated UUID extension
    Media->>DB: INSERT media metadata through tenant RLS connection
    alt Database insert fails after original write
        Note over FS,DB: Original file is not cleaned up [DECISION REQUIRED] AMB-044
        Media-->>Editor: Mapped database error
    else Media row inserted
        alt Detected MIME is JPEG, PNG, or WebP
            Media->>Image: Decode and generate configured WebP thumbnails
            Image->>FS: Write variant files
            alt Decode or variant write fails
                Note over FS,DB: Media row/original and any partial variants are not rolled back [PARTIAL] AMB-044
                Media-->>Editor: Processing error
            else Variants generated
                loop Each generated variant
                    Media->>DB: INSERT media_variants row
                end
                alt A variant row insert fails
                    Note over FS,DB: No transaction or compensating cleanup is implemented [PARTIAL] AMB-044
                    Media-->>Editor: Mapped database error
                else All metadata persisted
                    Media-->>Editor: Media detail with variants
                end
            end
        else PDF or text
            Media-->>Editor: Media detail without variants
        end
    end
end

rect rgb(238, 255, 242)
    Note over Consumer,DB: Public Delivery API cache hit, miss, and Redis fallback [IMPLEMENTED]
    Consumer->>Delivery: GET /api/v1/content, /pages, /settings, /navigation, sitemap, or robots
    Delivery->>DB: Resolve active default public organization
    Delivery->>Delivery: Normalize query and construct organization-scoped cache key
    Delivery->>Cache: get_or_set_json(key, TTL=300s)
    alt Redis connection unavailable
        Cache->>DB: Execute PostgreSQL fetch closure directly
        DB-->>Cache: Published tenant content/page/settings/navigation data
        Cache-->>Delivery: Uncached value
    else Redis connected
        Cache->>Cache: GET key
        alt Valid cached JSON
            Cache-->>Delivery: Cached value
        else Cache miss, Redis error, or invalid cached JSON
            Cache->>DB: Execute PostgreSQL fetch closure
            DB-->>Cache: Published data
            Cache->>Cache: Best-effort SETEX serialized value
            Cache-->>Delivery: Database value
        end
    end
    Delivery-->>Consumer: Public JSON/text response
    Note over Cache,DB: Redis failure degrades to PostgreSQL; no PostgreSQL delivery-cache table exists [IMPLEMENTED]
end

rect rgb(250, 248, 255)
    Note over Editor,DB: Webhook registration and SSRF-oriented URL validation [IMPLEMENTED]
    Editor->>Tenant: POST /api/webhooks with URL, events, optional secret
    Tenant->>Webhook: TenantContext
    Webhook->>Webhook: require_org_webhook_manager
    Webhook->>Webhook: Normalize/deduplicate supported events
    Webhook->>Webhook: Generate secret when absent; require at least 16 characters
    Webhook->>Webhook: Parse HTTP(S) URL, require host, reject credentials
    Webhook->>Webhook: Reject localhost/private/link-local/multicast/unspecified IP hosts
    alt Validation fails
        Webhook-->>Editor: Validation error; no row inserted
    else Validation succeeds
        Webhook->>DB: INSERT tenant-owned webhooks row with plaintext secret
        Webhook-->>Editor: Registered webhook including secret
    end
    Note over Webhook,Receiver: Validation checks literal host/IP; no DNS-resolution recheck is shown [PARTIAL]
end

rect rgb(255, 252, 238)
    Note over Webhook,Receiver: Signed webhook delivery [IMPLEMENTED, SINGLE ATTEMPT]
    Webhook->>DB: Open organization-scoped RLS connection
    Webhook->>DB: Load active webhooks subscribed to event
    loop Each matching webhook
        Webhook-->>Webhook: tokio::spawn asynchronous dispatch task
        Webhook->>Webhook: Serialize payload and HMAC-SHA256 sign with webhook secret
        Webhook->>Receiver: POST JSON with X-CMS-Event, X-CMS-Signature, X-Organization-Id; 10s timeout
        alt HTTP 2xx
            Receiver-->>Webhook: Success response
            Webhook->>DB: INSERT webhook_deliveries status=delivered and response details
        else HTTP non-2xx
            Receiver-->>Webhook: Error response
            Webhook->>DB: INSERT webhook_deliveries status=failed and response details
        else Network/timeout error
            Receiver--xWebhook: Request error
            Webhook->>DB: INSERT webhook_deliveries status=failed and error text
        end
        opt Delivery-log insert fails
            Note over Webhook,DB: Spawned task logs a warning; no durable retry or queue exists [PARTIAL] AMB-011
        end
    end
    Note over Webhook,Receiver: No retry scheduling or second attempt is implemented [PARTIAL] AMB-041
end
